			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: for all you high lvls<a name="37431"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Apr 30 04 3:55 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Keeping your instrument skills maxed is far more important than your weapon selection.
<br />

<br />
Groups won't invite a bard because of their melee DPS.
<br />
Songs are a bards most valuable asset.
<br />
If you can't sing your songs effectively (missed notes) or if you can't twist, you won't be very valuable to your group.
<br />

<br />

<br />
Your weapon choice is not all that important as long as youre not using complete garbage weapons. There's lots of sources for cash at low levels that you should be able to pick up some decent cheap gear in bazaar. Just be sure to check for recomended and required levels on the gear.
<br />

<br />
At low levels, it's best to use low delay weapons so your weapon skills will raise faster. You can sometimes find really good deals on low-end bard weapons like:
<br />

<br />
Sionachie's Partisan - 9/19 pierce
<br />
Sainy's Claw - 6/19 pierce
<br />
Symphonic Saber - 11/23 slash
<br />
Harmonic Dagger - 10/21 pierce
<br />

<br />

<br />
There is no single 'best' weapon type for bards.. just get the best weapon you can for your budget.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
