				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: for all you high lvls<a name="37446"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Apr 30 04 5:14 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>At level 7 it is hard to keep skill ups in line with your level.  I found that it was best to keep one primary skill as high as possible and when it maxxed switched to a secondary (1hs and piercing were my choices).  Eventually as you level these will max easily and you can switch in the last skill (1hb for me).
<br />

<br />
I didnt work on 1hb until level 51 or so and it is maxed now at level 57.  While it is a pain to start a new weapon at high levels, it is not the end of the world so long as you have an alternate weapon for those times you really need the extra DPS.  Most of the time you will not be providing significant DPS anyway and no one will notice  or care that you miss alot.
<br />

<br />
However you should keep your song skills up by level 20.  Spend the time to AFK train it is well worth the hastle.
<br />

<br />
</span></td>
