				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: for all you high lvls<a name="37487"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">May 1 04 10:13 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I agree whole heartedly with both Tinuvien and Harpsichord.  Having not only a 61 singer, but also 3 alts around 30ish, I must add something, however to what has been said.
<br />

<br />
Melee skills go up easy, Offense the same.  Instruments are nothing at all to up.  Defense is obnoxiously hard!  Take the time NOW while you are still low level to max up Defense at each level.  I didn't with my main, and am paying for it the hard way as mobs hit way to hard to let them hit me more than once or twice.  My weapon skills are maxed, but Defense is still about 50 points behind.
<br />

<br />
While you are still in these low levels grab about 3 or 4 blue mobs, Preferably low blue.  Pull them off to one side, near but not too near a guard and let them beat on you.  You will see defense skills go up quick that way, and can max for each level in a few minutes usually.  
<br />

<br />
IF you can keep it maxed per level up into the 20s you will be in good standing for the rest of your career.  But if you don't, you may be lacking will into the late 60s.  I did the above with my monk (level 35 now) and he is nearly as high in Defense as my bard was in the 50s.
<br />

<br />
Welcome to the class!
<br />

<br />
Tenosh on Prexus.
<br />
</span></td>
