				<td colspan="2"><span>A rather simple way to do it if you have not hit level 10.
<br />

<br />
Go out and attack a bunch (offence/deffence) or a single (wepon skill) of blues, yellow, reds and fight till you die<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" /> 
<br />

<br />
Then
<br />

<br />
Go out and atack a bunch of blues, yellow, reds and fight till you die
<br />

<br />
Then
<br />

<br />
Go out...   
<br />

<br />
I find this is a good way to bring up your skills fast.
<br />

<br />
At really young levels 1-3 attacking the little rats that skuttle around and have a number of them trying to kill you is a great way to bring up your offence and deffenc.. gives them a kick start.  
<br />

<br />
Before you hit Level 10 you can hunt a yellow, and kill the yellow after multiple deaths.  You can do this even with cloth armer as your only means of ac. 
<br />

<br />
If you are going to do this make sure your bind point is in the same zone as you or really close.   One trick is don't bother binding till you are finished with the noob area that has your defualt bind.
<br />
</span></td>
