			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: for all you high lvls<a name="38450"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">May 5 04 5:46 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Try to keep one weapon skill i.e. 1hs maxed (I chose 1hb just because of the Di'Zok Wristsnapper) until you hit 17 then you will get dual wield. You'll find the levels go too quickly to keep all of your skills up but don't worry about it too much...they'll slow down soon enough and your skills will start catching up. If you find 1hs is maxed let's say at level 10 start switching in a piercer or 1hb when the mob is in flee mode as you want to maximize your dps while you're being hit. I wouldn't actively use the 1hb or piercer while the mob is in your face though as this will cause you too much downtime post-fight. I would highly reccomend that you try and go straight up melee until as late as possible purely because of what others have said about not being able to take a hit at later levels due to crappy defense. So far my bard is level 29 and he has not used any form of kiting so far...but my defense and all weapon skills are maxed. I plan to melee until about level 40 which is when Defense will stop going up. You have plenty of time for kiting later <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-2.gif" border="0" alt="Big Smile" hspace="2" />
<br />

<br />
Like I said, once you hit 17 you get dual wield. Put your piercer or 1hb in your off-hand and let the skill go up that way. Every 5 skill ups switch your off-hand to the other weapon skill so the two skills you're not maxed in at least go up evenly. Eventually, and it might take a number of levels all will be maxed.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
